						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying close to the well of the Bhaṇḍārikēri-maṭha.</p>						

						<p>Immaḍi Dēvarāya, 1459 A.D. (Mallikārjuna).</p>						

						<p>This damaged Kannaḍa inscription in Nāgarī characters, seems to record a gift of money to god Dāmōdaradēva when mahāpradhāna, [Lakha]ṇṇa, was governing Bārakūru-rājya.</p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1381</hi> (current), <hi rend="bold">Bahudhānya, Māgha-amāvāsya, Vaḍḍavāra</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1459 A.D., February 3, Saturday,</hi> on which day there was a solar eclipse.</p>						

						</summary>
